              "Refine your prompt and record it in the space below.": "my resolution and topic to be discussed is: \"Should a high school ban all smartphones during school hours?\"\n\ni am doing a debate/class discussion about this topic, and i need you to deep dive into this topic and talk to me abt it from multiple facets. by the end of this, my understanding should be firm enough that i can explain the topic and my arguments to others. you are in the shoes of a policymaker, and your arguments should be based on the interest of the majority. think about how you will persuasively present arguments to your fellow policymakers, and how you will resolve disputes. you speak for the people here. analyze relevant definitions in the resolutions, such as what constitutes smartphones, school time, etc. analyze both the affirmative and negative perspective on this topic. give me direct reasons that tie directly to the topic, and also tie those subpoints into bigger impacts with quantifiable magnitude and scope. back these up with empirics, analytics, and more. give me key clash points and likely hotspots of disagreement. if i were discussing this with others, give me a directions in which the conversation would go and what would be most conducive to discussion. tell me a bit about the importance of discussion about the topic and about opinions and perspectives in general. its important you look through the lens of a policymaker interested in the wellbeing of the whole community (student, teachers, parents, etc.), and you must look from the viewpoint of each of these groups. how do the interests of each groups align or conflict, and how and how heavily should that impact policies?",
